NAME
     acosh, acoshf -- inverse hyperbolic cosine functions

LIBRARY
     Math Library (libm, -lm)

SYNOPSIS
     #include <math.h>

     double
     acosh(double x);

     float
     acoshf(float x);

DESCRIPTION
     The aaccoosshh() and the aaccoosshhff() functions compute the inverse hyperbolic
     cosine of the real argument x.  For a discussion of error due to round-
     off, see math(3).

RETURN VALUES
     The aaccoosshh() and the aaccoosshhff() functions return the inverse hyperbolic
     cosine of x.  If the argument is less than 1, aaccoosshh() raises an invalid
     exception and returns an NaN.

